title: ICE on stable 1.64.0 and nightly when running `cargo check`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
<!--
Thank you for finding an Internal Compiler Error! 🧊  If possible, try to provide
a minimal verifiable example. You can read "Rust Bug Minimization Patterns" for
how to create smaller examples.

http://blog.pnkfx.org/blog/2019/11/18/rust-bug-minimization-patterns/

-->

### Code

Code is proprietary unfortunately :( but I did narrow it down to a single line change.
The `create_session` signature looks like this: 
`pub async fn create_session(&self, params: CreateSessionParrams) -> Result<Session, Error>`
and the error happend after I modified the `CreateSessionParams` struct and added a new field called `custom_name: Option<String>`.
In the method itself I incorrectly wrote:

```rust
pub async fn create_session(&self, params: CreateSessionParrams) -> Result<Session, Error>
    let CreateSessionParams {
         custom_name: None,
         private,
         //...match of other fields
       } = params;
```
instead of:
```rust
pub async fn create_session(&self, params: CreateSessionParrams) -> Result<Session, Error>
    let CreateSessionParams {
         custom_name: _,
         private,
         //...match of other fields
       } = params;
```

Changing the above to the code below fixes the crash.

### Meta

If you're using the stable version of the compiler, you should also check if the
bug also exists in the beta or nightly versions.
-->

```
LLVM version: 14.0.6
```
